HEADWORD: Iliopsoas
<hw>Il`i*o*pso"as</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>The great flexor muscle of the hip joint, divisible into two parts,
the iliac and great psoas, -- often regarded as distinct
muscles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ilium</ent>⟦br⟧
